name: Baked Orange Salmon with Fennel
author: ellenmoriah
summary: A surprisingly good and healthy dish for guests or family. Salmon fillets are roasted with fennel bulb in an orange sauce.
ingredients: 1 small fennel bulb, trimmed and diced
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (150 degrees C)
In a medium skillet over medium heat, cook fennel in olive oil until translucent, about 20 minutes
Place the fillets skin side down in a glass baking dish
Pour the orange juice over the fillets
Sprinkle fennel over in an even layer, and season with
Cover the dish with aluminum foil
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork
